### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Create a new customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/customer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Miriam",
  "lastName": "Achieng",
  "email": "miriam@gmail.com",
  "phoneNumber": "0711592572",
  "address": "4060, chuka"
}

### 2. Create another customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/customer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "098-765-4321",
  "address": "456 Oak Ave, Town, State"
}

### 3. Get all customers
GET {{baseUrl}}/customer

### 4. Get customer by ID (replace {id} with actual customer ID from response above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/customer/1

### 5. Update customer (replace {id} with actual customer ID)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/customer/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "111-222-3333",
  "address": "789 Updated St, New City, State"
}

### 6. Delete a customer (replace {id} with actual customer ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/customer/1

### 7. Try to create customer with duplicate email (should return 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/customer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Duplicate",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "555-555-5555"
}

### 8. Try to get non-existent customer (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/customer/999

### 9. Create customer with missing required fields (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/customer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Missing",
  "email": "missing@example.com"
}